headlines.description: — Philadelphia opened a big lead, wasted it all, opened another big lead, wasted that one as well, then found itself in trouble midway through the fourth quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey scores 37, Embiid has 29 and Philadelphia rallies past Miami 109-105 to tighten East race

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson had 35 points and 11 assists, Josh Hart scored a season-high 31 points and the New York Knicks erased a 21-point deficit and beat the Sacramento Kings 120-109 on Thursday night to snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson, Hart help Knicks rally from 21-point deficit to beat Kings, snap three-game skid

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic finished with 25 points after a rare scoreless first quarter and the Dallas Mavericks stayed alone in fifth place in the Western Conference with a 109-95 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic finishes with 25 points after scoreless 1st quarter, Mavs beat Hawks 109-95

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Steph Curry and Klay Thompson scored 29 points each and the Golden State Warriors stretched their winning streak to a season-high six games with a 133-110 win over the Houston Rockets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry and Thompson score 29 each as Warriors stretch win streak to 6 with 133-110 win over Rockets

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 28 points, James Harden added 20 and the Los Angeles Clippers overcame an early 17-point deficit...
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Clippers overcome Jokic's triple-double and hang on to beat Nuggets 102-100
